The paper deals with collaborative inference in a sensor network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.MA) techniques. The focus is on coalition formation, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and social networks (cs.SI). The paper also considers a communication constraint, which is a common issue in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes an iterative algorithm, which falls under the category of optimization (cs.LG).
